 examining the complex relationships between traditional healing practices and biomedicine. Charles Piot's introduction contextualizes student-initiated development within the history of development work in West Africa since 1960, while his epilogue provides an update on the projects, compiles an inventory of best practices, and describes the type of projects that are likely to succeed. Doing Development in West Africa provides a relatable and intimate look into the range of challenges, successes, and failures that come with studying abroad in the global South.Contributors. Cheyenne Allenby, Kelly Andrejko, Connor Cotton, Allie Middleton, Caitlin Moyles, Charles Piot, Benjamin Ramsey, Maria Cecilia Romano, Stephanie Rotolo, Emma Smith, Sarah Zimmerman  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 0aEconomic assistance, AmericanzTogo. 0aEconomic development projectszTogo. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aMiddleton, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiddleton, Allie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamsey, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoyles, Caitlin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiot, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllenby, Cheyenne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCotton, Connor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndrejko, Kelly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRomano, Maria Cecilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiot, Charles, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZimmerm